				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">infiniteneslives wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You've got bankswitching, counter, multiplier, sound gen, and 1/2KB ram.</div>
<br />You forgot the most complex part (IMO): it keeps track of what the PPU is doing by watching the memory fetches, so that it can provide attribute data (attributes can be applied to individual tiles, rather than 16x16-pixel areas) and pattern data (512 tiles can be used for sprites and thousands can be used for the background instead of the usual 512 we have for everything) at the correct times.</div>

